protein. Furthermore, bat cells that were persistently infected with \u0394ORF5 MERS-CoV were resistant to superinfection by wildtype virus, likely due to reduced levels of the virus receptor, dipeptidyl peptidase 4 (DPP4) and higher basal levels of interferon in these cells. In summary, our study provides evidence for a model of coronavirus persistence in bats, along with the establishment of a unique persistently infected cell culture model to study MERS-CoV-bat interactions.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Banerjee, Arinjay", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Subudhi, Sonu", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rapin, Noreen", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lew, Jocelyne", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jain, Richa", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Falzarano, Darryl", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Misra, Vikram", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/4c2c7c3ecfa4a92c4cb98309bef330f5", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/eb582e50cccd8216c6f094f2cc5b24cfe39559031693f081e85e0e11bab71e18", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/H6PIQD2Q", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/H6PIQD2Q", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/e36181e26320caa918548ea89c43d203!/b175018-177582", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article"